1
00:00:10,875 --> 00:00:14,000
[NAMI breathes heavily]

2
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:22,333
[KURAMA] I'm gonna give you
a countdown... From ten.

3
00:00:22,416 --> 00:00:24,333
Nine.

4
00:00:24,416 --> 00:00:26,041
Come on.

5
00:00:26,125 --> 00:00:27,541
That's eight!

6
00:00:27,625 --> 00:00:29,166
Seven.

7
00:00:29,250 --> 00:00:30,375
Six.

8
00:00:30,458 --> 00:00:32,291
--I have to surrender.
--[KURAMA] Five.

9
00:00:32,375 --> 00:00:36,416
Wait. You know what?
Think I just changed my mind.

10
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:38,708
[gasps]

11
00:00:55,750 --> 00:00:57,291
Nami...

12
00:00:57,375 --> 00:01:00,875
I can feel your anger.
Your burning need for revenge.

13
00:01:00,958 --> 00:01:03,416
That murderous intent of yours.

14
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:06,541
It's like every shadow in
the jungle is filled with it.

15
00:01:06,625 --> 00:01:10,000
And that's why I gunned down
an innocent girl, Sagara.

16
00:01:10,083 --> 00:01:12,041
Just to piss you off.

17
00:01:12,125 --> 00:01:13,958
Kurama...

18
00:01:14,041 --> 00:01:16,416
[KURAMA] If you don't wanna
come out, that's fine.

19
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:17,875
You can hide in
this little shithole

20
00:01:17,958 --> 00:01:19,875
for the rest of your life.

21
00:01:19,958 --> 00:01:23,875
But first. Lemme tell
you what I plan to do.

22
00:01:23,958 --> 00:01:26,916
I'm gonna pay your real
girlfriend a little visit.

23
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:29,166
And I'm gonna give her
the same kinda treatment.

24
00:01:29,250 --> 00:01:30,708
He means Chidori!

25
00:01:30,791 --> 00:01:34,416
Yeah, that's right. I know where
she's being held right now.

26
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:35,916
And after this,

27
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:38,750
I'm goin' back there to drill
some holes in your woman.

28
00:01:38,833 --> 00:01:41,250
Just as tenderly as I
did with this little

29
00:01:41,333 --> 00:01:42,875
street urchin of yours.

30
00:01:42,958 --> 00:01:45,458
You piece of shit.

31
00:01:45,541 --> 00:01:47,916
[POLICE CHIEF]
I don't think he's coming.

32
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:50,291
Well in that case, let's go.

33
00:01:52,500 --> 00:01:54,166
[KURAMA]
Hm? Get down!

34
00:01:55,291 --> 00:01:56,625
[OFFICERS grunt]

35
00:02:04,083 --> 00:02:06,625
At least seven,
but possibly more.

36
00:02:06,708 --> 00:02:08,208
Who are they?

37
00:02:08,291 --> 00:02:11,333
Doesn't really matter.
Here's my chance!

38
00:02:13,458 --> 00:02:14,416
[gasps]

39
00:02:19,916 --> 00:02:21,041
[OFFICER G grunts]

40
00:02:21,125 --> 00:02:22,291
[OFFICER H]
Son of--

41
00:02:24,416 --> 00:02:25,916
[SOUSUKE grunts]

42
00:02:33,708 --> 00:02:35,541
[POLICE CHIEF whines]

43
00:02:48,083 --> 00:02:49,833
They're too far...

44
00:02:56,708 --> 00:02:58,416
[LEMON]
We're on the same side, Sousuke.

45
00:02:58,500 --> 00:02:59,875
[SOUSUKE gasps]

46
00:03:01,291 --> 00:03:02,833
[SOUSUKE]
Lemon?

47
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,708
What's going on here?

48
00:03:06,791 --> 00:03:08,416
[LEMON]
That talk can wait.

49
00:03:15,416 --> 00:03:21,083
[LEMON] Oh God.
I'm so sorry, Nami.

50
00:03:23,541 --> 00:03:28,875
[LEMON whimpers]

51
00:03:28,958 --> 00:03:31,583
If I'd just been
a little faster.

52
00:03:54,791 --> 00:03:58,166
[inaudible]

53
00:04:03,541 --> 00:04:07,708
[inaudible]

54
00:04:14,958 --> 00:04:17,708
My troops, they were completely
wiped out just like that.

55
00:04:17,791 --> 00:04:20,583
How'd this happen?
It doesn't make any sense.

56
00:04:20,666 --> 00:04:23,000
Did that Sagara guy
have backup all along?

57
00:04:23,083 --> 00:04:25,208
I have my doubts.
From what little I saw,

58
00:04:25,291 --> 00:04:27,166
it didn't look like they
were coordinating.

59
00:04:27,250 --> 00:04:29,291
It's probably a separate group.

60
00:04:29,375 --> 00:04:30,416
Well, if that's true,

61
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:31,791
then how'd they know
where to find us?

62
00:04:31,875 --> 00:04:33,125
[KURAMA]
How should I know?

63
00:04:33,208 --> 00:04:34,791
Hey, maybe this was a trap
that they were planning

64
00:04:34,875 --> 00:04:36,708
from the very beginning. Yeah.

65
00:04:36,791 --> 00:04:39,666
It must've been some kind of
trap, and Sagara was the bait.

66
00:04:39,750 --> 00:04:41,416
Thanks to bad information
on your end,

67
00:04:41,500 --> 00:04:43,250
I got baited into
a freakin' ambush,

68
00:04:43,333 --> 00:04:45,333
and all my troops ended
up getting massacred!

69
00:04:45,416 --> 00:04:46,875
[POLICE CHIEF grunts]

70
00:04:46,958 --> 00:04:48,833
Shut the hell up.

71
00:04:48,916 --> 00:04:50,250
I can't breathe.

72
00:04:50,333 --> 00:04:53,083
Listen closely. I'm extremely
pissed off right now.

73
00:04:53,166 --> 00:04:56,458
Those so-called troops of
yours turned out to be useless.

74
00:04:56,541 --> 00:04:59,250
And because of that,
Sagara's still alive.

75
00:04:59,333 --> 00:05:02,666
Plus, now I'm torn up  about
shootin' that poor girl.

76
00:05:02,750 --> 00:05:04,708
Maybe you don't get that.

77
00:05:04,791 --> 00:05:08,000
I bet a creep like you would
get off on that kind of thing.

78
00:05:08,083 --> 00:05:10,083
But I sure as hell don't.

79
00:05:10,166 --> 00:05:12,375
This shit'll haunt my
dreams for a long time.

80
00:05:12,458 --> 00:05:14,833
I wanted to ask about that.

81
00:05:14,916 --> 00:05:17,083
Why did you decide
to kill the girl?

82
00:05:17,166 --> 00:05:20,375
It seemed like we coulda
gotten more use out of her.

83
00:05:20,458 --> 00:05:22,791
[KURAMA]
She served her purpose.

84
00:05:22,875 --> 00:05:26,125
By killing her, I ensured
that he'd come after me.

85
00:05:26,208 --> 00:05:29,625
Given half a chance, I'm sure
he'd strangle me barehanded.

86
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:33,000
Please, sir...

87
00:05:33,083 --> 00:05:35,250
I'm going to lure
Sagara into town,

88
00:05:35,333 --> 00:05:38,416
and you're gonna help me
ambush him. Understand?

89
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:40,458
Yes, but I--

90
00:05:40,541 --> 00:05:43,791
[gasps, coughs]

91
00:05:43,875 --> 00:05:47,833
Mister Kurama. I demand that
you treat me with respect.

92
00:05:47,916 --> 00:05:49,708
I've done my part
for the organization,

93
00:05:49,791 --> 00:05:52,875
overseeing all operations
here in Namsac.

94
00:05:52,958 --> 00:05:54,916
I'm not some dog
for you to kick.

95
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:57,041
Yeah, sorry 'bout that.
You're right,

96
00:05:57,125 --> 00:06:00,375
it's just that your voice
really gets on my nerves.

97
00:06:00,458 --> 00:06:02,708
And for the record,

98
00:06:02,791 --> 00:06:05,458
you should try to be extra
polite when you talk to a man

99
00:06:05,541 --> 00:06:07,958
who's just quit smoking.

100
00:06:08,041 --> 00:06:11,500
I'm a lot more irritated than
you'd think from lookin' at me.

101
00:06:29,416 --> 00:06:32,125
[BARDET] Will that patch job
really get it moving again?

102
00:06:32,208 --> 00:06:34,125
[LEMON]
Should for a while, at least.

103
00:06:34,208 --> 00:06:37,583
That's amazing. Those old
Savages sure are tough.

104
00:06:45,666 --> 00:06:47,208
[ASCH]
I'm done here.

105
00:06:47,291 --> 00:06:48,958
[SOUSUKE]
Thanks.

106
00:06:49,041 --> 00:06:50,541
You going after them?

107
00:06:50,625 --> 00:06:52,083
[SOUSUKE]
Yes.

108
00:06:52,166 --> 00:06:56,666
All right, then...
Go get yourself killed.

109
00:06:57,875 --> 00:06:59,708
[RILEY]
I'm done too.

110
00:06:59,791 --> 00:07:01,125
Sorry.

111
00:07:01,208 --> 00:07:04,000
[RILEY] You can apologize
to Nami. I don't need it.

112
00:07:06,375 --> 00:07:07,791
[LEMON]
Sousuke.

113
00:07:07,875 --> 00:07:10,333
Can't help but notice,
you haven't asked who I am.

114
00:07:10,416 --> 00:07:12,666
[SOUSUKE]
I've already worked that out.

115
00:07:12,750 --> 00:07:16,250
You're most likely an agent
with the DGSE, based in France.

116
00:07:16,333 --> 00:07:17,791
[LEMON grunts]

117
00:07:17,875 --> 00:07:19,375
[SOUSUKE]
Looks like I'm right.

118
00:07:19,458 --> 00:07:21,708
Which means your friends
are an Action Division 29

119
00:07:21,791 --> 00:07:26,083
special forces team.
You're investigating Amalgam?

120
00:07:26,166 --> 00:07:27,666
[LEMON]
Yeah.

121
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:31,125
Sousuke Sagara. You're a pilot
with Mithril, is that right?

122
00:07:31,208 --> 00:07:34,375
I was with Mithril. Not anymore.

123
00:07:34,458 --> 00:07:36,375
Well anyway. You seem capable.

124
00:07:36,458 --> 00:07:38,333
If you're after that
Amalgam guy too,

125
00:07:38,416 --> 00:07:39,875
then let's capture him together.

126
00:07:39,958 --> 00:07:41,375
Capture's not enough.

127
00:07:41,458 --> 00:07:43,875
After everything that man's
done, he needs to be killed.

128
00:07:43,958 --> 00:07:46,250
He's a valuable
source of information.

129
00:07:46,333 --> 00:07:48,208
I don't take orders
from you guys.

130
00:07:48,291 --> 00:07:50,500
Kurama's mine,
and I will kill him.

131
00:07:50,583 --> 00:07:52,791
Look, I understand
how you feel,

132
00:07:52,875 --> 00:07:54,833
but if you go after those
guys by yourself,

133
00:07:54,916 --> 00:07:57,208
you'll be playing right
into their hands.

134
00:07:57,291 --> 00:07:59,625
[SOUSUKE]
I still have to try.

135
00:07:59,708 --> 00:08:01,708
See reason.

136
00:08:01,791 --> 00:08:05,458
[SOUSUKE] I'm sorry, but this
is all that I know to do.

137
00:08:14,250 --> 00:08:15,416
[LEMON]
Sousuke!

138
00:08:15,500 --> 00:08:18,583
We're still proceeding
with our own operation.

139
00:08:18,666 --> 00:08:20,250
[SOUSUKE]
Do what you want.

140
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:21,541
[ASCH, RILEY grunt]

141
00:08:46,041 --> 00:08:47,791
Stay focused.

142
00:08:56,791 --> 00:08:59,250
[OPERATOR A] Callin' us out
here in the middle of the night.

143
00:08:59,333 --> 00:09:00,666
Who's he think he is?

144
00:09:00,750 --> 00:09:03,833
Ehh, get over it. I hear
we're gonna make bank.

145
00:09:03,916 --> 00:09:04,958
[DAO]
Heh!

146
00:09:07,625 --> 00:09:09,291
[POLICE CHIEF]
Your attention!

147
00:09:09,375 --> 00:09:11,916
I called you all here
because I need warriors.

148
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,500
[OPERATOR A]
Warriors?

149
00:09:13,583 --> 00:09:14,750
That's right.

150
00:09:14,833 --> 00:09:18,416
Even as we speak, an AS
is approaching our city.

151
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:21,625
The operator is a
dangerous terrorist.

152
00:09:21,708 --> 00:09:24,125
He's in the grip of a
drug-fueled paranoia,

153
00:09:24,208 --> 00:09:26,041
and he's planning a rampage.

154
00:09:26,125 --> 00:09:28,333
[OPERATOR C] So, we just
need to kill the guy?

155
00:09:28,416 --> 00:09:32,000
Indeed. I want you fine men
to seek out this terrorist

156
00:09:32,083 --> 00:09:33,333
and bring him down

157
00:09:33,416 --> 00:09:36,250
before he can harm the
good people of Namsac.

158
00:09:36,333 --> 00:09:38,416
And be sure you
actually kill him.

159
00:09:38,500 --> 00:09:39,541
[OPERATOR C]
He's alone?

160
00:09:39,625 --> 00:09:40,541
[POLICE CHIEF]
That's right.

161
00:09:40,625 --> 00:09:41,875
[OPERATOR A]
Who the hell is he?

162
00:09:41,958 --> 00:09:45,625
[POLICE CHIEF chuckles]
Sousuke Sagara.

163
00:09:45,708 --> 00:09:48,166
Hold on. It's Sagara?

164
00:09:48,250 --> 00:09:51,833
And by the way, whoever can
score the killing blow,

165
00:09:51,916 --> 00:09:53,500
gets 30,000 extra.

166
00:09:53,583 --> 00:09:56,541
[OPERATORS cheer]

167
00:09:56,625 --> 00:09:59,583
[DAO] That's certainly
an appealing offer.

168
00:09:59,666 --> 00:10:01,625
It almost seems a
little too generous.

169
00:10:01,708 --> 00:10:03,500
[OPERATOR C]
There somethin' more to this?

170
00:10:03,583 --> 00:10:06,250
There's no need to
be concerned, gentlemen.

171
00:10:06,333 --> 00:10:09,500
We're providing you with all
the equipment you could need.

172
00:10:10,916 --> 00:10:13,375
[OPERATOR B] Wow, they've got
four of the latest Oerlikons.

173
00:10:13,458 --> 00:10:16,333
[OPERATOR C] I see OTO
Melaras, Mausers, Bofors.

174
00:10:16,416 --> 00:10:17,833
We've got it all.

175
00:10:27,791 --> 00:10:28,875
[POLICE CHIEF]
We got word.

176
00:10:28,958 --> 00:10:31,125
A white Savage was
seen passing a village

177
00:10:31,208 --> 00:10:33,208
fifteen kilometers
north of here.

178
00:10:33,291 --> 00:10:35,458
It looks like he wants
a fight after all.

179
00:10:35,541 --> 00:10:38,041
Like I said. He'll come.

180
00:10:38,125 --> 00:10:40,708
The only question now is
whether those clowns you hired

181
00:10:40,791 --> 00:10:42,416
will actually be of use.

182
00:10:42,500 --> 00:10:43,958
They'll destroy him.

183
00:10:44,041 --> 00:10:46,625
They have ten mechs armed to
the teeth, and his is damaged.

184
00:10:46,708 --> 00:10:47,791
He won't stand a chance.

185
00:10:47,875 --> 00:10:49,625
Well, I do hope you're right,

186
00:10:49,708 --> 00:10:52,041
but I should go make
some preparations.

187
00:10:52,125 --> 00:10:53,250
For what?

188
00:10:53,333 --> 00:10:55,375
[KURAMA] If he does
reach the finish line,

189
00:10:55,458 --> 00:10:57,208
then I'll greet him here.

190
00:11:05,125 --> 00:11:06,875
Kurama.

191
00:11:06,958 --> 00:11:09,125
[gasp]

192
00:11:09,208 --> 00:11:12,041
He sent a welcoming party.
Guess that confirms it.

193
00:11:12,125 --> 00:11:13,625
He's still in town.

194
00:11:21,708 --> 00:11:22,875
[OFFICER I]
Halt!

195
00:11:26,458 --> 00:11:28,250
[OFFICERS shout]

196
00:11:38,375 --> 00:11:40,166
[PEDESTRIANS shout]

197
00:11:40,250 --> 00:11:41,416
All right.

198
00:11:44,166 --> 00:11:46,375
[OPERATOR D]
Our man's just up ahead.

199
00:11:46,458 --> 00:11:48,208
I hear he's practically unarmed.

200
00:11:48,291 --> 00:11:51,416
[OPERATOR A] Sounds like I'm
about to be 30,000 bucks richer.

201
00:11:51,500 --> 00:11:52,666
[OPERATOR D]
Hold up,

202
00:11:52,750 --> 00:11:54,041
I thought we were
splittin' it fifty-fifty.

203
00:11:54,125 --> 00:11:55,291
[computer beeps]

204
00:11:55,375 --> 00:11:57,875
Huh? Behind us!

205
00:11:59,291 --> 00:12:00,666
[OPERATOR A]
Son of a bitch!

206
00:12:06,541 --> 00:12:08,333
[SOUSUKE]
Talk. How many more mechs?

207
00:12:08,416 --> 00:12:09,958
[OPERATOR A]
Screw you!

208
00:12:10,041 --> 00:12:13,166
[OPERATOR A gasps]
Stop it! Please! Eight!

209
00:12:13,250 --> 00:12:14,375
There are eight more!

210
00:12:14,458 --> 00:12:16,458
[SOUSUKE] Did you see a
man in a black coat?

211
00:12:16,541 --> 00:12:18,583
He's Asian. Pretty tall.

212
00:12:18,666 --> 00:12:21,666
[OPERATOR A] Yeah, he's at the
arena with the police chief.

213
00:12:21,750 --> 00:12:23,166
[OPERATOR C]
Yeah! Light him up!

214
00:12:23,250 --> 00:12:25,541
[OPERATOR A screams]
Wait, don't!

215
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:32,375
On to the arena.

216
00:12:45,625 --> 00:12:47,083
--[BARDET] Whoa.
--[LEMON gasps]

217
00:12:47,166 --> 00:12:50,750
[BARDET] This is Sagara's
handiwork? Quite a rampage.

218
00:12:50,833 --> 00:12:53,750
[LEMON] He isn't even
done yet. Look there.

219
00:13:00,666 --> 00:13:03,291
You bastard. Take this!

220
00:13:20,583 --> 00:13:22,041
You should've stayed home!

221
00:13:22,125 --> 00:13:24,125
[grunts]

222
00:13:43,833 --> 00:13:46,416
Get out of my way!

223
00:14:00,500 --> 00:14:01,625
Huh?

224
00:14:05,291 --> 00:14:07,166
Open fire, damn it!

225
00:14:08,458 --> 00:14:10,291
[OFFICERS shout]

226
00:14:10,375 --> 00:14:13,500
[POLICE CHIEF]
Stand your ground! Waa!

227
00:14:16,916 --> 00:14:18,041
[gasps]

228
00:14:18,125 --> 00:14:20,083
[DAO]
Sagara!

229
00:14:20,166 --> 00:14:24,291
[DAO yells]

230
00:14:30,291 --> 00:14:31,000
It's Dao.

231
00:14:31,083 --> 00:14:33,500
[DAO shouts]

232
00:14:37,750 --> 00:14:40,000
[POLICE CHIEF yelp, screams]

233
00:14:48,375 --> 00:14:50,833
[DAO]
I got you this time, Sagara.

234
00:14:50,916 --> 00:14:52,833
Now. Time to die!

235
00:14:59,125 --> 00:15:01,250
[SOUSUKE grunts]

236
00:15:05,333 --> 00:15:06,958
[DAO grunts]

237
00:15:08,625 --> 00:15:10,208
[SOUSUKE grunts]

238
00:15:13,666 --> 00:15:16,958
[SOUSUKE grunts]

239
00:15:17,041 --> 00:15:20,833
[SOUSUKE] The mech's systems.
They're back.

240
00:15:24,208 --> 00:15:26,625
[DAO laughs]

241
00:15:26,708 --> 00:15:28,625
Go to hell, bastard!

242
00:15:29,791 --> 00:15:34,750
[SOUSUKE grunts]

243
00:15:37,083 --> 00:15:40,041
Just a bit further. Keep moving!

244
00:15:42,666 --> 00:15:43,833
Now die!

245
00:16:19,166 --> 00:16:22,625
[SOUSUKE] Thanks, Nami.
Your mech was the best.

246
00:16:33,208 --> 00:16:36,458
[footsteps]

247
00:16:43,541 --> 00:16:45,916
[SOUSUKE grunts]

248
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:47,541
Where is he?

249
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:53,416
[SOUSUKE grunts]

250
00:16:53,500 --> 00:16:54,916
[SOUSUKE]
Up those stairs.

251
00:17:00,875 --> 00:17:02,041
[SOUSUKE grunts]

252
00:17:14,875 --> 00:17:16,000
[SOUSUKE grunts]

253
00:17:35,875 --> 00:17:37,416
[SOUSUKE grunts]

254
00:17:41,458 --> 00:17:43,125
He keeps retreating higher.

255
00:18:06,583 --> 00:18:08,083
[SOUSUKE gasps]

256
00:18:09,791 --> 00:18:12,208
[SOUSUKE] He could be
leading me into a trap.

257
00:18:15,125 --> 00:18:16,708
[SOUSUKE]
In that case...

258
00:18:22,750 --> 00:18:23,708
[gasps]

259
00:18:24,750 --> 00:18:27,500
[SOUSUKE grunts]

260
00:18:31,125 --> 00:18:32,291
[SOUSUKE gasps]

261
00:18:38,166 --> 00:18:43,125
[SOUSUKE grunts]

262
00:18:54,416 --> 00:18:56,166
[KURAMA grunts]

263
00:18:58,333 --> 00:19:00,458
[SWAT MEMBER B]
Drop the gun!

264
00:19:00,541 --> 00:19:05,500
[SWAT MEMBERS grunting]

265
00:19:09,375 --> 00:19:11,083
[SWAT MEMBERS groan]

266
00:19:21,416 --> 00:19:22,083
[SWAT MEMBER D grunts]

267
00:19:22,166 --> 00:19:23,416
[SWAT MEMBER E gasps]

268
00:19:29,625 --> 00:19:31,916
[SWAT MEMBER E] We got
to run! Get up! Get up!

269
00:19:34,458 --> 00:19:35,958
[KURAMA grunts]

270
00:20:11,958 --> 00:20:14,666
[SOUSUKE grunts]

271
00:20:14,750 --> 00:20:17,083
[SOUSUKE coughs]

272
00:20:18,875 --> 00:20:20,750
Where's Kaname Chidori?

273
00:20:20,833 --> 00:20:22,833
What'll you do if I say?

274
00:20:22,916 --> 00:20:24,083
[SOUSUKE]
Save her.

275
00:20:24,166 --> 00:20:26,958
[KURAMA] Hmph. Guess I
got killed by an idiot.

276
00:20:27,041 --> 00:20:28,333
Say it!

277
00:20:28,416 --> 00:20:32,041
I think I'd rather just
let you die in frustration.

278
00:20:32,125 --> 00:20:33,583
Tell me now!

279
00:20:33,666 --> 00:20:37,833
[KURAMA coughs] I shot you.
This makes no sense.

280
00:20:37,916 --> 00:20:40,625
How are you able t-to stand?

281
00:20:40,708 --> 00:20:42,125
[SOUSUKE]
Because of her!

282
00:20:42,208 --> 00:20:45,791
[KURAMA] Oh yeah? You think
it was the power of love?

283
00:20:45,875 --> 00:20:46,958
Don't make me laugh.

284
00:20:47,041 --> 00:20:48,666
It's not a joke!

285
00:20:54,541 --> 00:21:00,500
Try San Carlos. If not there,
then Niquero. Or Granada.

286
00:21:00,583 --> 00:21:01,958
Where else?

287
00:21:02,041 --> 00:21:04,333
How should I know?

288
00:21:04,416 --> 00:21:07,000
[KURAMA chuckles]
Could use a smoke.

289
00:21:07,083 --> 00:21:09,666
Should've never quit.

290
00:21:11,750 --> 00:21:15,208
[KURAMA exhales]

291
00:21:15,291 --> 00:21:18,333
[SOUSUKE grunts]

292
00:21:18,416 --> 00:21:22,708
San Carlos. Niquero. Granada.

293
00:21:25,583 --> 00:21:26,833
Sousuke!

294
00:21:26,916 --> 00:21:29,250
[SOUSUKE grunts]

295
00:21:30,625 --> 00:21:33,666
[LEMON] Bring an intubation kit!
I'll need atropine.

296
00:21:33,750 --> 00:21:35,625
And epinephrine, too!

297
00:21:38,041 --> 00:21:39,375
[SOUSUKE]
Nami?

298
00:21:41,875 --> 00:21:47,041
[SOUSUKE]
No... Chidori.

299
00:21:47,125 --> 00:21:50,708
I'm cold... I miss you.

300
00:21:50,791 --> 00:21:55,750
♪


301
00:23:21,666 --> 00:23:22,750
[HUNTER]
You're a punctual woman.

302
00:23:22,833 --> 00:23:25,375
I appreciate that.

303
00:23:25,458 --> 00:23:26,708
Were you followed?

304
00:23:26,791 --> 00:23:28,833
[WRAITH] I wouldn't have
come here if I was.

305
00:23:28,916 --> 00:23:30,833
[HUNTER]
Of course, just had to ask.

306
00:23:30,916 --> 00:23:33,666
So the cargo, is this it?

307
00:23:33,750 --> 00:23:35,000
[WRAITH]
Yes.

308
00:23:35,083 --> 00:23:37,000
[HUNTER] I'm amazed that
you managed to recover it.

309
00:23:37,083 --> 00:23:39,583
[WRAITH] The police were
busy running damage control.

310
00:23:39,666 --> 00:23:41,375
The only part of this
that gave me any trouble

311
00:23:41,458 --> 00:23:43,125
was getting it out of Japan.

312
00:23:43,208 --> 00:23:46,416
[HUNTER] Hm. Since you're here,
would you care to take a look

313
00:23:46,500 --> 00:23:48,708
at our cargo before
you head out?

314
00:23:48,791 --> 00:23:51,541
Bear in mind,
it's not finished yet.

315
00:23:51,625 --> 00:23:53,125
[WRAITH]
What's its name?

316
00:23:53,208 --> 00:23:54,375
[HUNTER]
It doesn't have one.

317
00:23:54,458 --> 00:23:56,708
I guess proper names are
reserved for projects

318
00:23:56,791 --> 00:23:58,791
that officially exist.

319
00:23:58,875 --> 00:24:01,500
That said, I think
it's safe to say what

320
00:24:01,583 --> 00:24:05,750
it's number would be.
The ARX-8.

321
00:24:09,291 --> 00:24:11,791
[SOUSUKE]
Next time: "The Fallen Witch."

